    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Cylinder Head And Valves -
        Cylinder Head Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Cylinder Head Assembly</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
            <title>Install Valve Assemblies</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The exhaust valve stems have a dimple on the valve head.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f1200458" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figEG2/EG2561.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Lubricating the Valve Stems</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Can</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Valve</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Intake Valve</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate the valves with clean engine oil. Insert the valve stems into their respective
                    valve guide bores in the cylinder head.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figF08/F0824.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Installing the Valve Seal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Seal</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Stem</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate the inner diameter of the new valve stem seals with clean engine oil. Install
                    the seals over each valve stem. Make sure the seal assembly is seated against the cylinder head
                    spring pockets.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f12004002" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figf08/F0819.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Installing the Valve Rotators</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Spring</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Rotator</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the valve spring over the stem seal assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the valve rotators.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figF08/F0823.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Installing the Valve Assembly Retainer Keys</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Spring Compression Tool</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Spring</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Assembly Retainer Key</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach the valve spring compression tool and compress the valve spring. Install the
                    valve assembly retainer keys and release valve spring compression tool. Make sure the retainer keys
                    are correctly seated on all valve stems.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">After valve inspection, reconditioning and replacement/installation, measure the valve
                    head recession relative to deck to confirm a good reconditioning job. Refer to the specifications.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
